        <p><h2>Student Outreach Service</h2></p>
        <p>The SOS program is for students who are seeking counseling from a peer in addition to, or in place of, a guidance counselor. There are 7-10 peer counselors available throughout the school day to counsel any student of Woodstock grades 7-12. These peer counselors are current older students who are selected by the counseling office and administrators to undergo training for counseling students in various topics. <br> Advisor: Nerissa Edwards</p> 
      </div>
